entence\": \"Just a few weeks ago, the chances of a successful Games in the City of Light seemed slim.\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 576, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France was in a political crisis.\", \"from\": 577, \"to\": 610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 577, \"end\": 583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999326451644945, \"rank\": 6.703362319204317e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Security officials were fearful of an attack.\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 656, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many French people seemed nonplussed.\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 694, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 662, \"end\": 675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee, under pressure from sponsors and broadcasters after Covid-19 led to largely spectator-less Games in Beijing and Tokyo, could barely afford another miss.\", \"from\": 696, \"to\": 885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 700, \"end\": 731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 833, \"end\": 840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\", \"score\": 0.7828991299591254, \"rank\": 0.2762397984878315, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\"}, {\"begin\": 845, \"end\": 850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3465229524895757e-21, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But as the Games draw to a close with a ceremony at the Stade de France on Aug 11, those fears appear little more than historical footnotes, with Paris rejuvenating the Olympic brand.\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 1070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1033, \"end\": 1038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9579889143820066e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"France surprised people,\\\" said Michael Payne, a former International Olympic Committee (IOC) marketing chief who has also worked with bid cities and sponsors, especially as recent Paris events such as the 2022 Uefa Champions League final had been marred by trouble.\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1073, \"end\": 1079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999326451644945, \"rank\": 6.703362319204317e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1104, \"end\": 1117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Payne_(executive)\", \"score\": 0.9998432523751143, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michael Payne\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Payne_(executive)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Payne_(executive)\"}, {\"begin\": 1128, \"end\": 1165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1128, \"end\": 1165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1253, \"end\": 1258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9579889143820066e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1278, \"end\": 1310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2022_UEFA_Champions_League_Final\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2022 Uefa Champions League final\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2022_UEFA_Champions_League_Final\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2022_UEFA_Champions_League_Final\"}, {\"begin\": 1288, \"end\": 1304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.812442888968949e-40, \"text\": \"Champions League\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It worked beyond anyone's wildest dreams.\\\"\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1383, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By avoiding costly white elephants, and prioritising temporary stadiums nestled among some of the world's most recognisable landmarks, French organisers have turned Paris into an open-air Olympic playground where everyone's invited, with or without a ticket.\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1520, \"end\": 1526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7861059485846884, \"rank\": 0.2719044494958339, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1550, \"end\": 1555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9579889143820066e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the sun rose, spectators would gather at the banks of the Seine to watch swimmers dive into the water, made just about swimmable at a cost of 1.5 billion euros ($1.64 billion).\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1706, \"end\": 1711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999545253, \"rank\": 4.516494183762135e-11, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As it set, tens of thousands of tourists thronged the Tuileries Garden, snapping selfies while the glowing Olympic cauldron began its nightly ascent into the purple-hued sky.\", \"from\": 1826, \"to\": 2000, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris has also avoided scandal, with geopolitical crises such as Ukraine and Gaza peripheral issues in the bubble of the Games while the U.S. election rollercoaster and riots in Britain hogged the headlines.\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2209, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2002, \"end\": 2007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9579889143820066e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2067, \"end\": 2074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999098381563, \"rank\": 9.016181392173029e-08, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 2079, \"end\": 2083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9958458804030051, \"rank\": 0.004171448292003811, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}, {\"begin\": 2139, \"end\": 2143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999837017658452, \"rank\": 1.6298499427811097e-05, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2180, \"end\": 2187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999999126885, \"rank\": 7.204308478867927e-11, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Payne said the success of Paris \\\"will reboot cities' interest in bidding to host the Games\\\".\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2303, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2237, \"end\": 2242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9579889143820066e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said he had already noticed several eyeing 2036.\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Turkey held a high-profile reception in Paris, which he described as the unofficial launch of Istanbul's bid, while \\\"(Indian Prime Minister) Modi is running around saying he has been offered the Games\\\", he said.\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2568, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2357, \"end\": 2363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.9999999997908162, \"rank\": 1.2981301900683955e-10, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}, {\"begin\": 2397, \"end\": 2402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9579889143820066e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2451, \"end\": 2459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\", \"score\": 0.9999999999681677, \"rank\": 3.21448733790657e-11, \"text\": \"Istanbul\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A spokesman for the Indian Olympic committee did not immediately respond to a request for comment.\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2590, \"end\": 2596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.994202706395887, \"rank\": 0.00558177202438263, \"text\": \"Indian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those tasked with following Paris seem impressed.\", \"from\": 2670, \"to\": 2719, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2698, \"end\": 2703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9579889143820066e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They have done a spectacular job,\\\" Los Angeles 2028 CEO Casey Wasserman told Reuters.\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2807, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2757, \"end\": 2773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Los Angeles 2028\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2778, \"end\": 2793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Casey Wasserman\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\"}, {\"begin\": 2799, \"end\": 2806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.482582818272605e-23, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The experience in the venues, which is what this is all about for the athletes and the fans, is world class.\\\"\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2918, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He said Los Angeles would not try to match Paris in style and substance but in \\\"authenticity and execution\\\", a view echoed by IOC President Thomas Bach.\", \"from\": 2920, \"to\": 3072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2928, \"end\": 2939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0136008369219013e-18, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 2963, \"end\": 2968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9579889143820066e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3046, \"end\": 3059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"IOC President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3060, \"end\": 3071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If LA would like to copy the Eiffel Tower, it would be a recipe for disaster,\\\" Bach said.\", \"from\": 3074, \"to\": 3164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3154, \"end\": 3158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.972180702687194e-14, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Each Olympic Games has to be authentic, has to be creative, has to show the culture of the host country.\\\"\", \"from\": 3165, \"to\": 3271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Los Angeles Mayor Karen Bass acknowledged Paris had set a high bar, and that LA's homelessness problems would be a challenge to overcome.\", \"from\": 3273, \"to\": 3410, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3273, \"end\": 3284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0136008369219013e-18, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 3291, \"end\": 3301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karen Bass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\"}, {\"begin\": 3315, \"end\": 3320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9579889143820066e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the City of Angels has one world class asset that nobody else can claim: \\\"We do have Hollywood, so I expect a lot of magical opportunities,\\\" she told Reuters.\", \"from\": 3411, \"to\": 3573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3500, \"end\": 3509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.450029115642713e-17, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3565, \"end\": 3572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.482582818272605e-23, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Broadcasters and sponsors, who were jittery after two COVID-blighted Games, are also thrilled.\", \"from\": 3575, \"to\": 3669, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"NBCUniversal, which has the largest Olympic media deal in the world after paying $7.65 billion in 2014 to extend its rights through 2032, scored its highest U.S. audience since 2012 and enjoyed record ad sales, with average total viewership for the first 14 days up 77% from Tokyo.\", \"from\": 3671, \"to\": 3952, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3671, \"end\": 3683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9999999999899956, \"rank\": 9.56200030905675e-12, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 3946, \"end\": 3951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3465229524895757e-21, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The number of viewers on Warner Bros.\", \"from\": 3954, \"to\": 3991, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3979, \"end\": 3985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Bros.\", \"score\": 0.9389651225728027, \"rank\": 0.06500228384565578, \"text\": \"Warner\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Bros.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Bros.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Discovery streaming platforms for the first two days of Paris exceeded the entire Tokyo Olympics, the company said.\", \"from\": 3992, \"to\": 4107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4048, \"end\": 4053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9579889143820066e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Games were Olympic sponsor Airbnb's biggest ever event in terms of guests accommodated in and around Paris, Emmanuel Marill, Airbnb's regional director for EMEA, told Reuters.\", \"from\": 4109, \"to\": 4288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4140, \"end\": 4146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Airbnb\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\"}, {\"begin\": 4214, \"end\": 4219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9579889143820066e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4221, \"end\": 4229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\", \"score\": 0.9999999233950831, \"rank\": 7.630703623222616e-08, \"text\": \"Emmanuel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\"}, {\"begin\": 4238, \"end\": 4244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Airbnb\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\"}, {\"begin\": 4269, \"end\": 4273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Bros._Discovery_EMEA\", \"score\": 0.9998031896268127, \"rank\": 0.00019684911544322358, \"text\": \"EMEA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Bros._Discovery_EMEA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Bros._Discovery_EMEA\"}, {\"begin\": 4280, \"end\": 4287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.482582818272605e-23, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is a kind of magic that happened,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 4290, \"to\": 4340, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dory Ellis Garfinkle, chief marketing officer at brand strategy firm Siegel+Gale, said Paris is a \\\"comeback Olympics\\\" for advertisers, with data showing 300% growth in searches for brands during the opening ceremony compared to Tokyo.\", \"from\": 4342, \"to\": 4576, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4429, \"end\": 4434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9579889143820066e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4570, \"end\": 4575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3465229524895757e-21, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris' success is a major relief for the IOC, which had been struggling to attract younger audiences needed to justify multi-billion-dollar TV and sponsorship deals.\", \"from\": 4578, \"to\": 4743, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4578, \"end\": 4583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9579889143820066e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4619, \"end\": 4622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.247678143512382e-40, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It successfully navigated a potentially risky move to deepen product placement, with no major backlash over Samsung phones on medal podiums or Louis Vuitton suitcases during the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 4745, \"to\": 4940, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4853, \"end\": 4860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"score\": 0.9999999999708962, \"rank\": 2.8993663886734556e-11, \"text\": \"Samsung\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Expect more in future Games, IOC officials say.\", \"from\": 4941, \"to\": 4988, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4970, \"end\": 4973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.247678143512382e-40, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Paris was not faultless.\", \"from\": 4990, \"to\": 5018, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4994, \"end\": 4999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9579889143820066e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although the worst case scenario of a militant attack was avoided, a mysterious rail and telecoms sabotage at the start of the Games remains unsolved.\", \"from\": 5020, \"to\": 5170, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some residents in Seine-Saint-Denis, France's poorest administrative department where the Olympic Village was located, said that despite organisers' efforts to bring them closer to the Games, they felt left out.\", \"from\": 5171, \"to\": 5382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5189, \"end\": 5206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\"}, {\"begin\": 5208, \"end\": 5214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999326451644945, \"rank\": 6.703362319204317e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 5261, \"end\": 5276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2888076728721917e-30, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Payne said the deluge during the opening ceremony was a setback, but less damaging than the parody of Leonardo Da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper\\\" which upset some Catholics.\", \"from\": 5384, \"to\": 5551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5486, \"end\": 5494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 0.9999990587434577, \"rank\": 9.41257339135228e-07, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 5495, \"end\": 5503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.308065422692109e-28, \"text\": \"Da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 5541, \"end\": 5550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999987900062524, \"rank\": 1.1594071518703808e-06, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also highlighted athletes' complaints about Olympic Village food.\", \"from\": 5552, \"to\": 5620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5599, \"end\": 5614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2888076728721917e-30, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But if these are your only problems, you can deal with it,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 5622, \"to\": 5691, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Games provided a welcome fillip to President Emmanuel Macron, who plunged France into political chaos with his snap legislative election just weeks before the Olympics.\", \"from\": 5693, \"to\": 5865, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5742, \"end\": 5757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 5771, \"end\": 5777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999326451644945, \"rank\": 6.703362319204317e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the honeymoon is unlikely to linger.\", \"from\": 5867, \"to\": 5907, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France remains under a caretaker government, with the Games merely postponing the political crisis.\", \"from\": 5909, \"to\": 6008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5909, \"end\": 5915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999326451644945, \"rank\": 6.703362319204317e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A post-Olympics hangover beckons for France's entire political class, with budget cuts, awkward parliamentary alliances and voter dissatisfaction ahead.\", \"from\": 6009, \"to\": 6161, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6046, \"end\": 6052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999326451644945, \"rank\": 6.703362319204317e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Senator Laure Darcos said the Games would provide no uplift to Macron's popularity.\", \"from\": 6163, \"to\": 6246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6171, \"end\": 6183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Darcos\", \"score\": 0.9999998530411284, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laure Darcos\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Darcos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Darcos\"}, {\"begin\": 6226, \"end\": 6232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.852235350241058e-25, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He's going to try to profit from the aura of the Olympics,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 6248, \"to\": 6318, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The craze for the Olympics is real, but I do not think it will benefit him at all.\\\"\", \"from\": 6319, \"to\": 6403, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS  Olympics  French politics  Media  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 6404, \"to\": 6562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6423, \"end\": 6429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7861059485846884, \"rank\": 0.2719044494958339, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"